!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

concert /ˈkɒnsət/

(concerts) 

1. N-COUNT A concert is a performance of music. 音乐会 

例： ...a short concert of piano music. …一场简短的钢琴音乐会。 

例： I've been to plenty of live rock concerts. 我到过很多现场摇滚音乐会。 

2. PHRASE If a musician or group of musicians appears in concert , they are giving a live performance. 现场演出 

例： I want people to remember Elvis in concert. 我希望人们记住现场表演的埃尔维斯。

